  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dc5\u0db3 \u0db7\u0dcf\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9 \u0d85\u0db4\u0db1\u0dba\u0db1\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Merchandise exports are on the rise",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka's merchandise exports in June 2022 have become 1.2 billion US dollars. Here, the growth of garments and textiles, rubber and coconut related products is noticeable.",
        "In June 2021, that figure was one billion US dollars. Considering this, the annual growth has become 20 percent.",
        "Also, considering the first six months of 2020, 2021 and 2022, merchandise exports have grown to 4.4, 5.7 and 6.4 billion US dollars respectively.",
        "However, tea exports have declined. The export of diamonds and gems has grown by 100 percent from 20.33 million US dollars to 40.72 million US dollars.",
        "Also, processed food and beverages have grown from 26.70 to 45.52 million US dollars and seafood exports have grown from 15.77 to 36.39 million US dollars."
      ],
